margin-top:7px;margin-bottom:3px">授業形態</div></td><td width="50" align="center"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">講義</div></td></tr><tr><td width="100" align="center" bgcolor="lightsteelblue"><div style="margin-top:7px;margin-bottom:3px">授業実施方法</div></td><td colspan=3 width="450" align="left"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">&nbsp;&nbsp&#9745対面&nbsp;&nbsp&#9744オンデマンド&nbsp;&nbsp&#9744同時双方向<br></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4" width="580"><div style="margin:10px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">ディプロマ・ポリシーとの対応</div><div style="margin:10px">&#9744&nbsp1.&nbsp人間，文化，社会を理解し，それらを技術的観点から考察する能力と技術を新しい生活につなぐ強い使命感・責任感，高い倫理観<br>&#9744&nbsp2.&nbsp現象の理解・操作のための数理的基礎知識と科学的素養<br>&#9745&nbsp3.&nbsp国内外の人々と対話できるコミュニケーション力と論理的思考力<br>&#9744&nbsp4.&nbsp（高度工学教育課程のみ）基幹となる専門分野の基盤的な知識・技術とこれによって課題を解決する能力，新たな知識・技術を習得する能力<br>&#9744&nbsp4.&nbsp（創造工学教育課程のみ）基幹となる専門分野の基礎知識と他の分野の知識・技術を関連づけ多面的に見ることで新たな価値を創出する能力<br></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4" width="580"><div style="margin:10px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">授業の目的・達成目標</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>【授業の目的】</p>
<p>This course emphasizes communicative evaluation and analysis. The overall goal of the course is to improve student ability to understand and produce extended discourse in English, especially in reading and writing contexts. Academic English vocabulary, recognizing and summarizing key points, critical thinking skills, and logical argumentation based on examples and evidence will be emphasized.</p>
<p>【達成目標】</p>
<p>Students will</p>
<p>・acquire greater skills in reading articles in English and knowledge about a variety of current topics,</p>
<p>・enlarge their academic vocabulary and improve their ability to understand the grammatical structure of sentences and paragraphs, and</p>
<p>・gain experience in writing their opinion on current topics.</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">授業計画</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>Weeks 1, 2, and 3: Unit 1 Sports and Fitness</p>
<p>              - 1A The World's Game - Analyzing Infographics (1)</p>
<p>              - 1B What Makes an Olympic Champion? - Scanning for Specific Information</p>
<p>              - Review Quiz</p>
<p>              - Video: Sport Climbing</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Weeks 4, 5, and 6: Unit 2 Skin Deep</p>
<p>              - 2A What is Beauty?- Analyzing a Writer's Claims</p>
<p>             - 2B Skin: The Body's Canvas - Summarizing the Main Idea of Paragraphs</p>
<p>             - Unit 2 Review Quiz</p>
<p>             - Video: The Beauty of Ugly Food </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Week 7: Work shop - Different Ways of Articulation</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Weeks 8, 9, and 10: Unit 3 Animals in Danger</p>
<p>            - 3A Racing to Rescue Koalas - Determining the Meaning of Unfamiliar Words</p>
<p>            - 3B Tracking the Snow Leopard - Annotating a Reading Passage</p>
<p>            - Unit 3 Review Quiz</p>
<p>            - Video: Protecting Pandas</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Weeks 11, 12, and 13: Unit 4 Violent Earth</p>
<p>           - 4A Sacred Summits - Summarizing a Text</p>
<p>           - 4B Is Prediction Possible? - Analyzing infographics (2) </p>
<p>          - Unit 4 Review Quiz</p>
<p>          - Video: Earthquakes 101</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Weeks 14 and 15: Unit 5 Islands and Beaches</p>
<p>          - 5A Land of Fire and Ice - Summarizing Details on a Map</p>
<p>          -5B The Perfect Beach - Identifying a Writer's Point of View</p>
<p>          - Unit 5 Review Quiz</p>
<p>          - Video: Ha Long Bay</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Contents may be changed according to the level of students.</p>
<p> </p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の方法</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>Vocabulary Checking: 30%, Note-taking: 40%, Assignments: 30%</p>
<p> </p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の基準</div><div style="margin:10px">秀　 達成目標を超えた成果を上げている　100点～90点<br>優　 達成目標に十分達している　　　　　89点～80点<br>良　 達成目標に達している　　　　　　　79点～70点<br>可　 達成目標に概ね達している　　　　　69点～60点<br>不可 達成目標に達していない　　　　　　59点以下<br><p>The teacher will explain the grading system in class. Based on a maximum score of 100, grades will be awarded as follows:</p>
<p>S (Excellent) 90-100</p>
<p>A (Very good) 80-90</p>
<p>B (Good) 70-80</p>
<p>C (Pass) 60-70</p>
<p>D (Fail) Below 60.</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">事前・事後学修等の指示及び履修にあたっての注意事項</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>Self Preparation: Check the words in the textbook while answering the questions. (120 min.)</p>
<p>Review: Make note in English in your notebook to make sure you understand the passage. (120min.)</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">教科書</div><div style="margin:10px"><a href="http://opac.lib.nitech.ac.jp/opc/recordID/catalog.bib/NB02228326" target=_blank>Reading Explorer 3, Third Edition, National Geographic Learning<a><br></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">参考書</div><div style="margin:10px"></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">オフィスアワー</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>By appointment.</p>
